                deposit my paycheck into an account without participating in the fractional 
                reserve banking system that has been destroying our economy. That's why 
                virtual nzd exists, deposit cash or pay with a credit card and hold your 
                own virtual dollars in a decentralized banking system denominated in 
                new zealand dollars. This is not a stable coin, it is an asymmetric asset
                with a floating exchange rate. 
                <br/><br/>
                Use decentralized exchanges to convert between
                virtual nzd and anything from Bitcoin to USDT, the echange rate on these exchanges 
                is set automatically by the supply and demand curves for each currency, and in some cases 
                you may be able to get a better deal buying through an exchange compared to buying through 
                this payment gateway. We will always charge exactly $1 for 1 nzd. We only provide a fiat
                on-ramp, we DO NOT provide any method of cashing back out of nzd into either cash or bank deposits, 
                the virtual nzd is not intended to be a separate asset class to physical cash. As such 
                we do not try to peg the cash out exchange rate to $1, and discourage holding this asset 
                in the hopes of making money via speculation. 
                <br/><br/>
                If you do need to cash out you can use any centralized
                exchange that offers nzd deposits, or via an over-the-counter transactions with a private buyer.
                <br/><br/>
                The long term goal of this asset class is to kill the Australian banks suckling on our economy.
                <br/><br/>
                Fuck those ozzy cunts.
                </p>
